        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 3 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of strong
thunderstorms extending from 9 miles north of Montoya to 11 miles
north of Sumner Lake State Park, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Tucumcari and Montoya.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 40 between Mile Markers 302 and 329.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 92 and 102.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Heavy rains from severe thunderstorms can produce sudden and
dangerous flows in arroyos, ditches and over low water crossings. Do
not attempt to drive through areas where water covers the roadway.</instruction>
